            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are some of the key trends in renewable energy for 2026:\n\n1. **Energy Storage**: Advances in battery technology and long-duration energy storage systems are crucial for balancing intermittent sources like wind and solar. This trend is supported by next-gen lithium-silicon and sodium-ion batteries [StartUs Insights](https://www.startus-insights.com/innovators-guide/renewable-energy-trends/).\n\n2. **Solar Energy Integration**: Innovations such as perovskite solar cells, floating solar farms, and Building-Integrated Photovoltaics (BIPV) are expanding solar energy use beyond traditional panels [Renewable Energy Conference](https://www.renewableenergyconference.org/blog/trends-in-renewable-energy-2026.html).\n\n3. **Green Hydrogen**: Increasingly viewed as a solution for decarbonizing hard-to-abate sectors, green hydrogen is becoming more viable due to declining electrolyzer costs and expanding hydrogen hubs [pw-magazine USA](https://pv-magazine-usa.com/2025/10/30/five-trends-that-will-shape-renewable-energy-in-2026/).\n\n4. **AI and Smart Grids**: The integration of AI and IoT in energy management is improving grid reliability and efficiency, enabling real-time demand response and decentralized energy markets [S&P Global](https://www.spglobal.com/energy/en/news-research/special-reports/energy-transition/horizons-top-cleantech-trends-2026).\n\n5. **Offshore Wind Expansion**: Both fixed and floating offshore wind technologies are capturing deeper waters with robust energy potential, especially in regions like the North Sea and U.S. East Coast [Renewable Energy Blog](https://www.renewableenergyconference.org/blog/trends-in-renewable-energy-2026.html).\n\n6. **Policy Shifts and Investments**: Governments are adapting policies to facilitate energy transitions, often focusing on capital and operational efficiency while managing supply chain challenges [Deloitte Insights](https://www.deloitte.com/us/en/insights/industry/renewable-energy/renewable-energy-industry-outlook.html).\n\nThese trends highlight the continuous evolution in technology, policy, and market dynamics driving the renewable energy sector forward.",
